```

## Add dependencies and refresh gomod2nix

Within this app directory:

```
cd projects/apps/{{ name }}
go get example.com/some/module@latest
go mod tidy
```

Then from repo root, regenerate glue and `gomod2nix.toml` deterministically:

```
build-tools/tools/dev/install-deps.ts
```

This script will:
- Export the Buck graph, sync providers, and regenerate `third_party/providers/auto_map.bzl`.
- Generate or update `gomod2nix.toml` based on the current `go.mod`/`go.sum`.

## Patching a Go dependency

Use the repo patch tool to start a patch workspace, then apply a canonical patch:

```
build-tools/tools/bin/patch-pkg start go golang.org/x/net
# Make edits in the workspace as directed by the tool
build-tools/tools/bin/patch-pkg apply go golang.org/x/net
```

Patches are stored under `projects/apps/{{ name }}/patches/go/` and are consumed directly by the Go Nix template. No provider sync is required for Go; just rebuild after applying a patch.

## Repository layout

- `projects/apps/{{ name }}`: CLI source, its `go.mod`, and `TARGETS` using `nix_go_binary`.
- `projects/libs/*`: Libraries consumed by apps; each owns its `TARGETS`.
- `projects/apps/{{ name }}/patches/go/`: Canonical Go dependency patches created by `patch-pkg` for this package.

## Providers and glue

`nix_go_*` macros build via Nix with local patches applied from this app’s `patches/go/` directory. Glue generation (`export-graph`, auto-map) is primarily used for Node importer‑scoped providers; Go no longer requires provider sync.